CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper November 10, 1962, pg. 20, reads: "Two Future Panthers - James Jones, left, 265-pond tackle, and halfback Eric Crabtree, right, get a few pointers from Pitt's freshman coach, Bill Kaliden.  Both Jones and Crabtree are expected to play key roles in the grid destiny of the Panthers in 1963. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: University of Pittsburgh football players no. 78 James Jones, and no. 32 Eric Crabtree, standing on either side of freshmen football coach Bill Kaliden, vertical format
